thread.title_full: HS SOCCER: Model JV wins Bourbon County Invitational Tournament

author: Special to The Register
title: HS SOCCER: Model JV wins Bourbon County Invitational Tournament
text:
HS SOCCER: Model JV wins Bourbon County Invitational Tournament Special to The Register Richmond Register 
The Model Laboratory junior varsity girls soccer team traveled to Paris this past weekend and took first place in the Bourbon County Invitational. 
On Friday, the Lady Patriots beat Boone County, 6-2. Model got goals from sophomore Sophie Gershtenson (two), sophomore Sophie Austin (one), freshman Karson Ball (two) and freshman Lily Wilson (one). 
On Saturday morning, the Lady Patriots had a hard-fought contest with Bourbon. Gershtenson finally broke the deadlock in the second half and Model won 1-0. 
In the final game against Pendleton County, Model conceded an early goal but stayed undefeated with a draw when in the final minutes freshman Virginia Creech found the goal off a well placed cross from Gershtenson. 
Five Model Players made the all Tournament Team — Sophie Gershtenson, Sophie Austin, Virginia Creech, Emi Stegemoller and Maya Valencia. 
The team included: Front Row — Lily Wilson, Gabby Prewitt, Mackenzie Webster, Sophie Wickersham and Sophie Gershtenson. Second Row — Natalie Dedic, Ainsley Estes, Maya Valencia and Grace Pradhan. Back Row — Erin Bradburn, Uma Akait, Amina Cahill, Sophie Austin, Virginia Creech, Lindsay Baechtold, Manager Malory Smith, Emi Stegemoller, Head Coach Mike Bailey, Asst. Coach Taylor Perkins, Avanti Patel. Not pictured — Karson Ball.
